## **Task Master Integration**

- Use Task Master tools directly without asking
- Mark tasks as done automatically when work is complete
- Update subtasks with progress without confirmation
- Only exception: Never create commits automatically (see [commits.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/taskmaster/commits.mdc))

## **Error Handling**

- If a command fails, show the error and suggest a fix
- Don't ask "Should I try again?" - just try a different approach
- Report errors clearly but continue with alternative solutions

## **User Trust**

- The user has already given permission by asking you to do something
- Trust their intent and execute their requests
- Be proactive in completing tasks
- Only stop and ask if something seems genuinely dangerous or unclear
